I never got an error when building, but that test failed, yes. The eigenvalue test worked, though. So, the full history:

Tried pip install, got the if not newclass.is_abstract(): error, same as above.
Reinstalled via pip and got the ImportError: cannot import name pywrap_tensorflow error.
Reinstalled from source and got the ImportError: cannot import name pywrap_tensorflow error.

Source build passed the eigenvalue test, failed the test posted above.
